# Document Data Contract

- `DocumentData` is the single source of truth for frontend data shape.
- Every document JSON must include all required contract fields.
- Use strict mapping from raw JSON into `DocumentData` in data loaders.
- Keep `categorySlug` and mapped `categoryId/category` synchronized.
- `metaTitle` and `metaDesc` may contain `{year}` and should be rendered with current year.

## Validation Expectations

- `slug` must be unique among all documents.
- `relatedIds` should reference existing document slugs only.
- `published` controls visibility in routes, homepage blocks, and sitemap.
- `updatedAt` must be present for `lastModified` in sitemap.
- Form fields should use supported types only: `text | select | date | number`.

## Migration Rule

- Switching from mock JSON to DB/Prisma must not change UI component contracts.

## File Scope

- `src/types/index.ts`
- `src/data/categories.json`
- `src/data/documents/*.json`
- `src/lib/mock.ts`
- `src/app/api/generate/route.ts`

## Block Conditions

- Do not merge content where `categorySlug` has no matching category.
- Do not merge content where `parentSlug` references a non-existent hub.
- Do not merge content where `relatedIds` include unknown slugs.
- Do not remove required fields to satisfy temporary UI shortcuts.

## Done Criteria

- Route generation works for all `published: true` documents.
- `sitemap.xml` includes only published entries with valid URLs.
- `npm run lint` and `npm run build` pass.
